13/08/2004
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- The co-ordinator of the International Criminal Tribunal for the Former Yugoslavia's office in Serbia-Montenegro, Aleksandra Milenov, has announced the preparation of 11 new indictments.
According to a press statement released Thursday (12 August), the investigations involve crimes against Serbs and Albanians in Kosovo as well as crimes committed in Bosnia and Herzegovina and Serbia-Montenegro during the conflicts in the former Yugoslavia.
Milenov also repeated a request to Serbian authorities to arrest and hand over four Serb generals -- Nebojsa Pavkovic, Vladimir Lazarevic, Sreten Lukic and Vlasimir Djordjevic -- as well as wartime Bosnian Serb military leader Ratko Mladic.
(Tanjug, Beta - 12/08/04)
